HEADWORD: Sancho pedro
<hw>Sancho pedro</hw>. <ety>[Sp. <ets>Pedro</ets> Peter.]</ety>
<fld>(Card Playing)</fld> <def>A variety of auction pitch in which the
nine (<xex>sancho</xex>) and five (<xex>pedro</xex>) of trumps are added
as counting cards at their pip value, and the ten of trumps counts
game.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanctificate</ent>⟦br⟧
